      "content": "hey i keep noticing something weird with my search queries lately. like, every time i start typing something about \"supply chain logistics\" or \"quantum encryption,\" the autocomplete suggestions aren't just following my history... they're almost like they're anticipating words that don't even make sense in context, but feel weirdly specific. like, i'll type \"quantum\" and the third suggestion is something totally unrelated to tech but feels coded. u ever see anything like that in the data patterns?",
